<DOCNO> NYT19990304.0009 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 00:07 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7160 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKC-HOUSTON-UNCC-HNS &LR;      03-04 0743
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-HOUSTON-UNCC-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Houston wilts in second half
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By JERRY WIZIG &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 1999, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
BIRMINGHAM, Ala. _ They would have preferred sticking around a
little longer. Instead, the Houston Cougars packed up early and
headed home.
</P>
<P>
   The Cougars' first-round game in the Conference USA tournament
on Wednesday hinged on a dead-battery start to the second half and
was terminated 75-51 by North Carolina Charlotte at the
Birmingham-Jefferson Civic Center.
</P>
<P>
   Their fourth consecutive loss to close the schedule included the
12th-seeded Cougars' lowest scoring output of a 10-17 season. The
49ers, the fifth seed, won their 19th game against 10 losses and
solidified their chance for at least an at-large berth in the NCAA
Tournament. After all, they came in with a No. 24 RPI and the
nation's 12th-toughest schedule.
</P>
<P>
   UH, on the other hand, exited with its fourth straight
first-round loss in the postseason, dating to the 1996 Southwest
Conference tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``We would have liked to have stayed for the weekend, but this
wasn't our game. We came out flat,'' said Clyde Drexler, who
concluded his first season as UH coach. ``We had a couple of guys
who were injured and not at the top of their game. Injuries are
part of the game that you deal with.''
</P>
<P>
   In the Cougars' case, that was a difficult task with guard Gee
Gervin, an all-conference first-teamer and league leader in scoring
and assists, severely limited by a recurring left-heel injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was do-or-die, and I tried to give as much as I could,''
said Gervin, who spent the last seven minutes of the game on the
bench, a towel over his face to mask his dejection. ``The
tournament is when you always want to be at your best, and I
haven't been lately.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm looking forward to being back next season with the guys
and with coach Drexler,'' added Gervin, seemingly dispelling any
rumors he might pass up his senior season to enter the NBA draft.
``I'm going to spend the offseason getting as strong as I can.''
</P>
<P>
   As was the case most of the season, Gervin was constantly
doubled and at times even triple-teamed, preventing his passing
off. Defended much of they day by 6-7 senior Galen Young or 6-6
Marlon Thomas, Gervin was held to 5-of-13 shooting, 13 points and
zero assists with eight turnovers. The 49ers thus limited Gervin to
11-of-29 accuracy in two meetings, including a two-point UNCC win
last week.
</P>
<P>
   With 6-9 forward William Stringfellow in early foul trouble and
6-9 Kenny Younger playing on a bruised knee suffered during the
game, UH struggled to score.
</P>
<P>
   ``UNCC was very aggressive on defense and on the boards,''
Drexler said. ``They had way too many offensive rebounds,
especially in the first half (a 13-3 margin), and we couldn't get
it done.''
</P>
<P>
   Younger (18 points, 11 rebounds in the entire 40 minutes) was
practically the Cougars' only man on the boards after Stringfellow,
C-USA's No. 2 rebounder, had two early fouls before adding his
third and fourth personals 8{ minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
   UNCC's Young (15 points, 12 rebounds) and 6-8 senior Kelvin
Price (19 points, seven rebounds, three blocked shots) were too
physical for the Cougars. Said UNCC's Bobby Lutz, who like Drexler
is in his first year as his team's head coach: ``We'd never be
where we are without those two guys.''
</P>
<P>
   And Lutz feels as certain as a coach without an automatic NCAA
bid can be about reaching the Tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``In my mind, there aren't any (doubts),'' he said. ``We felt we
needed to win today, but I felt we were already in.''
</P>
<P>
   Lutz said UH's first-half change to a 1-3-1 trap helped get the
Cougars back from an early 21-9 deficit to within 23-20.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a great move, and we didn't handle it well,'' Lutz
said. ``But it didn't bother us in the second half.''
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers also shot 52 percent in the second half. The Cougars,
meanwhile, scored just 10 points in the first 10 minutes after
halftime and trailed 55-36 when Stringfellow exited on his fifth
personal with 11:37 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   UH, which had pulled within 31-26 at halftime, missed a slam by
Stringfellow to start the second half and went downhill from there.
Back-to-back treys by Treva Crosby and Gervin got them within 38-32
before UNCC's 23-6 run wrapped it up.
</P>
<P>
   ``We took our lumps this year,'' said Drexler. ``I thought we
did the best we could with what we had to work with.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
