<HEADLINE>
UA'S TERRY NAMED PLAYER OF YEAR 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By LEE SHAPPELL  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TUCSON _ Arizona point guard Jason Terry has been named National
Player of the Year in college basketball by ``Sports Illustrated''
in this week's issue.
</P>
<P>
   Terry, a 6-foot-2 senior guard who has carried the Wildcats to a
No. 13 ranking and the brink of their 15th straight NCAA Tournament
bid, joins Andre Miller of Utah, Evan Eschmeyer of Northwestern,
Elton Brand of Duke and Wally Szczerblak of Miami (Ohio) on the
``SI'' All-America first team.
</P>
<P>
   Also this week, Terry was named one of 17 finalists for the John
R. Wooden Award, presented by the Los Angeles Athletic Club.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's got a definite shot at several of these national player
of the year awards,'' UA Coach Lute Olson said. ``Some of them,
more than likely, will depend on play in the NCAA Tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``When we recruited Jason there's no way I'd have said that he'd
ever average 20 points. He was not a shooter or a scorer when he
came in. Jason has had the willingness to put in the hours to
improve his shooting. He's making it a possibility that he'll be an
NBA draft lottery pick. He's certainly a lottery prospect.''
</P>
<P>
   Terry said that he hopes to erase any doubts as to his
worthiness by leading the Wildcats on a long run into the NCAA
Tournament.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hopefully I can help us play great,'' Terry said. ``Nobody
believes we can go very far. We might have a surprise.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's nice to be mentioned for these awards. Hopefully, with a
great tournament run, I'll live up to it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``S''I's Grant Wahl wrote that Terry, who leads the Pac-10 in
scoring (22.2), assists (5.58) and steals (2.65), received the nod
over Miller because ``no other player in the country is as crucial
to his team's success.''
</P>
<P>
   Wahl added that ``Terry's numbers are better than Miller and he
plays in a far tougher conference.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Besides,'' writes Wahl, ``who would you want to take your last
shot? Terry has given Arizona a tie or the lead in the last 10
seconds three times this season.''
</P>
</TEXT>
