<HEADER>
A7211 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-     03-04 0430
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
QUINT SHOWS HE BELONGS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB MCMANAMAN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - During the preseason, it appeared he was on the
trading block. Four teams were rumored to be in the chase. But with
each passing week and every month that followed, it became clear
that Coyotes defenseman  &UR; Deron Quint wasn't going anywhere.
</P>
<P>
   Except to a new position, left wing, which he has played for the
past five games.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a big difference in the positions, but as long as I'm out
there, I'm happy,'' said Quint, who scored a goal, his third,
during the Coyotes' 3-2 loss in Boston on Tuesday. ``I'm definitely
not complaining about the ice time. Playing with JR  &UR; (Jeremy
Roenick) and  &UR; (Rick) Tocchet, there's not much that can go wrong.''
</P>
<P>
   Quint's days as a forward could be numbered, however. Although
Quint has done reasonably well at the position, left wing  &UR; Greg
Adams could be back Friday against the visiting Detroit Red Wings.
</P>
<P>
   Adams has missed the past week because of a pulled groin muscle,
but he has been skating on his own and is ready to return. &QL; 
The untouchables &QL; 
A bunch of the Coyotes' game-high 51 hits left some of the Bruins
bitter with seemingly every other check. A couple in particular by
Roenick and  &UR; Keith &UR; Tkachuk steamed Boston players like a piping hot
plate of clams.
</P>
<P>
   Tkachuk lined up  &UR; Anson Carter with a clean hit, which  &UR; Jason
Allison instantly took exception with, and the two high-priced
forwards dropped the gloves and duked it out.
</P>
<P>
   ``If they're going to dish it out, they're going to have to take
it, too,'' Allison said. ``A lot of those guys, they think they're
untouchable.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't mind if he fights Tkachuk,'' Bruins Coach  &UR; Pat Burns
said. &UR; ``I don't want him fighting bozos. If he's going to fight,
fight the Tkachuks, fight the Roenicks, but don't bother with these
Quint guys and these  &UR; (Shane) Doan guys.'' &QL; 
Slap shots &QL; 
Detroit Red Wings forward  &UR; Sergei Fedorov has been suspended for
five games without pay for slashing the New York Islanders'  &UR; Zdeno
Chara during Saturday's game.
</P>
<P>
   Fedorov will lose $386,178 in pay. His suspension begins Friday
against the Coyotes and ends March 17 when the Coyotes visit
Detroit.
</P>
<P>
   Fedorov has been classified as a repeat offender, given that he
was suspended for two games on March 26 for a hit from behind on
 &UR; Jason Marshall of Anaheim.
</P>
<P>
   Center  &UR; Rob Murray has been sent back to Springfield. Murray was
a healthy scratch Tuesday. &QL; 
Associated Press contributed to this report. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
