<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-04 02:36 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7271 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKERS-WRITETHRU-     03-04 0655
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-WRITETHRU-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS WIN AGAIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ It was an uneasy marriage at first, the Lakers and
Dennis Rodman, and complicated by a change in the head of household
with the arrival of surrogate father-coach Kurt Rambis.
</P>
<P>
   But the Lakers promptly won four straight, and Lakers executive
Jerry West gave his blessing, pleased with what he called the
honeymoon period.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers are making it a long vacation.
</P>
<P>
   They're now 5-0 in the Rodman-Rambis era after defeating the
Phoenix Suns for the second straight game, 101-95 at the Forum.
</P>
<P>
   And they have Danny Manning to thank in part for the victory.
Two nights earlier, Manning chided Kobe Bryant as ``too short'' to
guard him. Bryant took it personally, to the tune of 23 points in
the second half, leading a second straight comeback win.
</P>
<P>
   He finished with a game-high 32, plus several choice words to
Manning and the Suns bench.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't like that man,'' Bryant said of Manning's putdown.
``People go and say things like that, I don't appreciate it too
much.''
</P>
<P>
   Fired up by it?
</P>
<P>
   ``Hell, yeah.''
</P>
<P>
   It showed, as Bryant slammed down tomahawk dunks and shot glares
and words at Manning.
</P>
<P>
   Not that he needed extra motivation, but there was also the
matter of keeping a winning streak intact and defending the home
court. The Lakers fell to a 34-25 deficit after one quarter and
trailed 55-49 at halftime before Bryant took over.
</P>
<P>
   His jumper failing him in a 2-for-7 first half, Bryant went to
the more direct approach to start the third quarter _ taking it to
the hole three straight times and scoring 11 consecutive points as
the Lakers gained the lead for the first time, 68-65.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't want to lose the game,'' he said. ``There was no way
in the world I was going to let them come back and have revenge on
our home court. Everybody on the team felt the same way, so we all
just picked it up.''
</P>
<P>
   Shaquille O'Neal added 27 points and Rodman grabbed a
season-high 17 rebounds. Clifford Robinson led the Suns with 20.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns led by three points early in the fourth when Rick Fox
brought the Lakers back with eight straight points, including two
3-pointers, to make it 81-78. Bryant followed with six straight to
complete a 16-5 run and give the Lakers an 89-81 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix never got closer than four points after that.
</P>
<P>
   All that remained for the Lakers was to ponder this sudden need
for come-from-behind wins. For the second straight game, they were
slow out of the gate.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is something we're concerned about,'' Rambis said. ``We
want to be known as a team that comes at you straight out of the
box.''
</P>
<P>
   Every marriage, of course, will have its rough spots. Rambis is
realistic about the length of this honeymoon.
</P>
<P>
   ``Eventually, the first loss is going to happen,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   That moment will have to wait.
</P>
<P>
   Rambis was fortunate not to have suffered his first career loss
two nights earlier in Phoenix, when the Lakers had to overcome an
eight-point deficit in the fourth quarter to beat the Suns.
</P>
<P>
   Hard on his players, hard on himself, Rambis said he was
partially to blame for the near-defeat.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wasn't real happy with the way I prepared the team to play
in Phoenix,'' he said. ``We didn't get out of the gate really well.
We didn't execute the way we're capable of executing.... There's a
lot of things we didn't do, and I take responsibility for that.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was even less happy after I watched the videotape of the
game. I let (the players) know _ we won, but that doesn't mean that
everything's OK. We took a little step back.''
</P>
<P>
   The problems weren't solved in one game, but the progress is
there. Maybe all they need is another quip from Manning.
</P>
<P>
   ``Have I settled my score with him?'' Bryant said. ``I don't
know. Maybe he'll say something else.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
