   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-MONICA _ LONDON _ Former White House intern Monica
Lewinsky comes to Britsh television live on Thursday. And we'll be
watching. Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in the lifestyle (l) and international (i)
categories.
</P>
<P>
   PEOPLE-BIRTHDAY _ People, the ``mother of all human interest
magazines,'' turns 25 years old Friday (March 5). It's the magazine
that most shrewdly anticipated and capitalized on our national
obsession with celebrity. People was a punchline in ``The Big
Chill,'' when it served as an emblem for empty fluff (''It's just
good investigative journalism'' deadpanned Jeff Goldblum, who
played a People reporter), but, in fact, has expertly gauged what
we want to read about. With 33 million readers and spinoffs such as
InStyle and Teen People going strong, and ongoing expansion into
television and cyberspace, the franchise looks durable. A look at
the People phenomenon. (Emerson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
