</P>
<P>
   COXNET-ENTERTAINMENT 0305 _ A preview of the South by Southwest
music conference in Austin, Texas. Now into its 13th year, SXSW has
become firmly established as the most well-attended national music
conference in the country. A look at what the event means to the
record industry, the participating bands, the city of Austin and
the fans who come to hear the music. Featuring photos of bands
scheduled to perform along with the most popular venues. (McLeese,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FATHERS _ Father rarely knows best on prime-time television any
more. Fathers are central, recurring figures on only 15 of 102
prime-time network comedies or dramas, and only four of these
programs portray the dad as both competent and caring, the National
Fatherhood Initiative recently reported. (Dart, Cox Washington
Bureau)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO REVIEWS _ Drew Barrymore plays a 16th-century French lass
whose wealthy dad dies, leaving her at the mercy of evil stepmom
Anjelica Huston and a couple of snooty stepsisses. Yeah, you know
the drill. ``Ever After'' is the story of Cinderella. But this time
out, there's no fairy godmother with a wand helping Danielle play
dress-up at the ball. (Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) With 1
column color studio photograph from the film.
</P>
<P>
   CD REVIEWS _ It's been seven years since XTC's last studio
album, ``Nonsuch,'' but the band's world is much the same. Now down
to a duo, XTC still concocts pastoral pop that never fails to call
to mind the two musical B's of the '60s: the Beatles and Beach
Boys. (Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHEAST-INNS _ A thumbnail review of 10 inns in the Southeast.
(Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
