<HEADLINE>
`THE CAR' MAY BE REVVING UP FOR A SEQUEL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What's the name of the movie starring James Brolin about a
car that's killing people?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.G., Fort Worth, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The film is 1977's ``The Car,'' which also stars Ronny Cox
and Melody Thomas Scott.
</P>
<P>
   The film doesn't appear to be available on video, but it still
airs occasionally on TV. The Sci-Fi Channel aired it in late
January.
</P>
<P>
   The movie should be easier to find if a planned sequel is
filmed. The Internet movie site Coming Attractions reported last
year that writers Brad Heiner and Robert Masciantonio are working
on a script for ``The Car 2.''
</P>
<P>
   The story reportedly brings back the demonic 1971 Lincoln Mark
III, and Brolin has been approached to star in it. You can find
Coming Attractions on the World Wide Web at corona.bc.ca//films.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What's the address of people that I could send Christmas
cards to?
</P>
<P>
   _ I.P.
</P>
<P>
   A: Greeting cards of all kinds can be sent to St. Jude's Ranch
for Children (in Nevada), where they are converted into new cards
for Christmas and other holidays.
</P>
<P>
   The ranch, a nonprofit home for troubled and abused children,
started the project about 25 years ago to teach residents about
earning money. Profits are used for field trips and savings
accounts for the residents.
</P>
<P>
   The 50 residents at the ranch produced 300,000 cards last year.
Send packages to 100 St. Jude's St., Boulder City, NV 89005, and
first-class mail to Box 60100, Boulder City, NV 89006.
</P>
<P>
   A 10-card packet of cards can be ordered for $6.50 from the
second address or by calling (800) 492-3562.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How can I contact the woman who makes fruitcakes in the shape
of Texas? She was on ``Texas Country Reporter,'' but I missed
almost all of the story.
</P>
<P>
   _ R.J., Azle, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Those fruitcakes are made by Gladys' Cookie Shop in Flatonia.
For ordering information, call (800) 580-9596, or write to 11624 N.
State Highway 95, Flatonia, TX 78941.
</P>
<P>
   ``Texas Country Reporter'' airs at 5 p.m. Sundays on
WFAA/Channel 8 (ABC) and on 19 other stations around the state.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions about the show, call (800) 839-2713 or
visit the show's World Wide Web site at
www.texascountryreporter.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) .MDBU/ nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
