<P>
   KOSOVO-U.S. (Jakarta, Indonesia) _ Developments on U.S. policy
in Kosovo. By Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-VIOLENCE (Belfast) _ As the formal peace process moves
ahead in Northern Ireland, horrific ``punishment'' beatings by
Catholic and Protestant militias are on the rise. These groups fear
that if true peace comes they will lose control of their
neighborhoods. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-YELTSIN (Moscow) _ President Boris N. Yeltsin dismissed
Boris A. Berezovsky, intensifying a power struggle that has roiled
the capital. One of Russia's most powerful and cocksure tycoons,
Berezovsky has been serving as the chief executive of the
Commonwealth of Independent States, a largely ineffectual
organization of former Soviet republics. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-ZHU (Beijing) _ Zhu Rongji, the Chinese prime minister,
will give a speech opening the National People's Congress. By
Elisabeth Rosenthal.
</P>
