</P>
<P>
   w/RTP-SAS _ CARY, N.C. _ The fitness staff at SAS Institute
Inc., the big software maker, was torn over hardware. Should they
buy more exercise bikes or rowing machines? Such seemingly small
decisions are a big deal at SAS, where many of the 2,700 employees
in Cary, N.C., work as programmers of statistical software. With
sales this year forecast to reach $1 billion, the nation's largest
privately held software producer sells to thousands of businesses,
universities and government agencies worldwide. (Burritt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
