<P>
   NEWT _ FONG PAC, as Newt Gingrich's new political action
committee is known, is circulating a new fund-raising letter,
advertising an April 14 ``Salute to Newt'' gala in Washington. For
$5,000 a year, the federal limit for PAC contributions, donors get
to attend up to six of the PAC's advisory board meetings, plus ``an
invitation to join Newt and Marianne for an annual retreat.'' But
there's more. The appeal also makes clear that Gingrich's PAC
welcomes so-called soft money, large, unregulated contributions
from corporations and individuals. It provides a handy place for
contributors to check whether they are giving $10,000, $25,000 or
$50,000. (Sherman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
