   INTERNET-SCHOOLS _ WASHINGTON _ The Senate Commerce Committee
holds a hearing on a bill that would require schools and libraries
with Internet access to install filtering software. Opponents say
that would inhibit access to legitimate research materials as well
as smut. (Glass, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
