<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV-SWEEPS (Undated) -- Monica Lewinsky's carefully orchestrated
campaign to cash in on her notoriety is off to a blockbuster
beginning. An average audience of 48.5 million Americans were
planted in front of their TV sets Wednesday as President Clinton's
ex-paramour bared her soul on ABC's ``20/20.'' By Don Aucoin. 920
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DELL-IBM (Undated) _ In one of the largest arrangements of its
kind, Dell Computer Corp. will buy an estimated $16 billion worth
of equipment from International Business Machines Corp. as the
computer makers jointly develop new technology. By Ronald
Rosenberg. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   RETAIL-SALES (Undated) _ With consumers continuing to spend
freely, retailers had another strong month in February, with
discount chains leading the way. By Chris Reidy. 700 words.
