<HEADLINE>
WHAT CASTS LOVE ASUNDER
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Lynn Redgrave &LR; , 56, has filed for divorce after learning that
66-year-old  &UR; John Clark &LR; , her husband of 32 years, had fathered a
child by his personal assistant, who later married his son and
became his daughter-in-law.
</P>
<P>
   ``We really were one big happy family, of sorts,'' Clark told
the New York Daily News. It was last Thanksgiving, he said, that he
told Redgrave that the 4-year-old child was his. ``She was busy
cooking the turkey. We had guests. The entire holiday was pretty
awful.''
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, he said he was glad about his actions. ``My kids
were so slow giving us grandkids. I had to make our own.'' (See Who
Said What for more marital speculation.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONICA MOMENTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Our five favorite moments from ``Monica's Story'' by &UR; Andrew &LR; 
 &UR; Morton &LR;  (St. Martin's; $24.95):
</P>
<P>
   _ The president told Monica about scars from his unhappy
childhood, when chubbiness caused him to run so slowly that he
never got any chocolate eggs at Easter.
</P>
