   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 03/04/99. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT38) KIEV, Russia -- March 04, 1999 -- UKRAINE-ASYLUM, 3-04
-- Pavlo Lazarenko at his office in Kiev before he fled last month.
Lazarenko, the former Ukrainian prime minister who asserts that the
nation's leaders are using corruption charges to persecute him,
says Thursday that he has cleared the first procedural hurdle
toward winning political asylum in the United States. (James
Hill/New York Times Photo)
</P>
