during the bands opening song ``Jumping Jack Flash'' on Wednesday.
The Stones are currently in the midst of their tour titled ``No
Security.'' (Ernst Peters/The Lakeland Ledger)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) PALO ALTO, Calif. -- March 04, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN.
MARCH 7 -- BIZ-PROFILE-REID, 3-04 -- Thomas S. Reid points out a
one-year-old sappling at the foot of a redwood tree in Palo Alto.
Reid, 51, is one of a new breed of environmentalists who to rely on
the power of scientific and economic information in their quest to
save endangered species or limit pollution. Last week, these groves
were saved from the chainsaws and mills in a last-minute deal with
the government. (Thor Swift/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) NEW YORK -- March 04, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN. MARCH 7 --
KIDS-TRAINING, 3-04 -- Federica Bautista, left, who shares a
two-bedroom apartment in Queens with seven relatives, set up a
pushcart vending business that helps support her mother and her son
after completing a program run by the National Foundation for
Teaching Entrepreneurship. She and her son, Abraham, visit with a
cousin, Victor Aguilar, center, and her brother Hermilo. (Linda
Rosier/New York Times Photo)
</P>
