``20 Dates.'' By bending the rules to send up the conventions of
romance, Berkowitz, 36, produced a movie that defies genre labels.
``It's a screwball romantic comedy, it's a document of single life
today, it's guerrilla filmmaking,'' says Berkowitz, 36, who found
