in Tennessee Williams' ``Not About Nightingales,'' at Circle in the
Square on Broadway. As staged by Trevor Nunn, the artistic director
of the Royal National Theater in London, the production is so
spectacularly realized that it both serves the play and celebrates
the Williams career, for which it can be seen as a kind of gaudy
preface. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
