Peden was a victim of punishment beatings, a practice where members
of the paramilitary armies that control working class neighborhoods
in this conflicted British province turn their violence not on
their declared enemies from the other side of the religious divide
but on their own. (Carlos Lopez-Barillas/New York Times Photo)
