<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Interview ratings beat expectations
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Barbara Walters' interview with Monica Lewinsky was
the most-watched newsmagazine show in TV history, ABC News'
research department estimated Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   About 70 million people watched some or all of the two-hour
``20/20'' interview Wednesday night, according to ABC's analysis of
Nielsen Media Research figures. That doesn't quite elevate the
Lewinsky interview to the levels of a Super Bowl or a ``Seinfeld''
finale, but it is much higher than most analysts expected.
</P>
<P>
   In metro Atlanta, viewership was even higher than the national
average. About 50 percent of the TV sets in use in Atlanta were
tuned to the Lewinsky interview, according to Nielsen. That
compares with 34 percent that watched George Clooney's final
episode of ``ER'' two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   _ Phil Kloer writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
