<HEADLINE>
U.S. CRITICIZES BUILDUP OF SERBIAN TROOPS 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Clinton administration officials say a Serbian
buildup of nearly 10,000 troops on the northern border of Kosovo
could severely limit any attempt to use force to back up diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said they feared that Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic might be preparing either to attack the Kosovo Albanian
fighters or to try to prevent NATO troops from entering Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't know exactly why they're there,'' said the Pentagon
spokesman, Kenneth H. Bacon. ``They're both not good reasons.''
</P>
</TEXT>
