were filed by Juanita Brodderick last week.
 &HT;    ''Clinton has not denied them as any decent man would,' says Pat
Trueman, who directed Bush Administration obscenity prosecution. He
sees no hope of change: ``There are few rapists concerned with the
problem of pornography in America. We have not had obscenity
prosecution and we should not expect them from a morally bankrupt
president.''
 &HT;    
