gives her spin on the process. ``There are many second-generation
Indian Americans who find that the arranged marriage question
travels across the seas to perch persistently on their doorsteps,''
she writes. She however, is not entirely convinced by either course
of action. But secretly, she hopes love will win the debate in her
own case.
</P>
<P>
   Moved as BC-ARRANGED-MARRIAGES-NEWAMERICA-NYTSF in ``k''
commentary, ``a'' general news and ``l'' lifestyle files.
</P>
